Graph Neural Networks (GNNs) are powerful tools for processing graph-structured data, but their effectiveness is limited by the availability of large-scale labeled datasets. This research aims to address this challenge by developing a novel framework for generating synthetic graph datasets with controlled properties and varying levels of labeled data.

