Previous approaches have focused on using existing datasets or developing frameworks for handling large graph datasets, but they have not addressed the specific challenge of generating synthetic datasets with controlled properties and sufficient labeled data. The complexity of graph structures and the need for realistic properties have made this problem difficult to solve.

