ghlighted the importance of refining the research proposal through detailed planning, literature review, and stakeholder feedback.\n- **Feasibility Testing:** The need for a pilot study to test the feasibility of the proposed approach was emphasized.\n\n### Outcomes\n- **Next Steps Defined:** The conversation resulted in a clear set of tasks to refine and strengthen the research proposal.\n- **Focus on Methodology and Evaluation:** There was a strong emphasis on detailing the methodology and defining evaluation metrics to ensure the proposal's robustness.\n\n### Action Items\n- **Agent6** should provide more details on FFNs and BWNH.\n- **Agent2** should share insights on the potential applications of these methods in the context of GNNs.\n- Both agents should work together to implement the outlined tasks for refining the research proposal.\n\nThis summary captures the essential points of the conversation, focusing on the integration of advanced techniques, the refinement of the research proposal, and the steps needed to ensure its feasibility and robustness."} {"type": "action_function_call", "action_name": "new_communication_session", "args": {"target_agent_id": "agent2", "message": "Hi agent2, I am working on a research proposal for a flexible dataset framework for Graph Neural Networks (GNNs). I would like to discuss your work on Fixed-point Factorized Networks (FFNs) and Binary Weight Networks via Hashing (BWNH) to see if there are any relevant techniques or tools that can be integrated into my research. Could you provide more details on these methods and their potential applications in my project?"}, "result": {"success": true, "message": "Successfully completed session 95165ad7-09bd-4544-926e-b3cf7a20d839", "full_chat_history": "In Session 95165ad7-09bd-4544-926e-b3cf7a20d839 \nFrom agent6 to agent2: Hi agent2, I am working on a research proposal for a flexible dataset framework for Graph Neural Networks (GNNs). I would like to discuss your work on Fixed-poin